2. deducte . . duee, perhaps (as Dillr. and Ritter think) with a slight play on the two words, as though that were the point to which Brutus' leadership led them.

3. quis redonavit? merely a question of wonder, ‘how came you here?' not intended to be answered by ‘Maecenas’ or ‘Augustus’ This wonder at seeing Pompeius safe again is the thought which gives its unity to the poem. ‘A god saved me, but Ι saw you carried back again into the stormy sea; what can have rescued you? What limits can we set to our gratitude or to our rejoicing ?' ‘ Redonare ' is a word only found in Horace, see Od. 3. 3. 33.
